        "category": "Nature",
        "desc": "One of Ontario's most visited provincial parks and a true four-season destination just minutes from Huntsville. In summer: Stubb's Falls trail through stunning glacial terrain, sandy swimming beaches on Arrowhead Lake, canoe and kayak rentals, biking trails, and family camping on 1,237 hectares. In winter: a magical 1.3 km illuminated skating trail winding through the boreal forest, cross-country skiing, snowshoeing, and tubing. Algonquin Park is 30 minutes away. 290,000+ visitors in 2022 make this one of Ontario's most loved parks. Electrical sites, cabins, and backcountry camping available.",
